P(A) = 0.5
P(A \cup (B^c \cap C^c)^c)=0.8
P(A^c \cap (B \cup C))
(B^c \cap C^c)^c = (B \cup C)
P(X \cap Y^c) = P(X^c \cap Y)
A
A\cup B\cup C
\begin{align}P\bigl(A^c\cap(B\cup C)\bigr) &= P(A^c\cap A)+P\bigl(A^c\cap(B\cup C)\bigr)\\ &= P\bigl(A^c\cap (A\cup B\cup C)\bigr)\\ &= P\bigl((A\cup B\cup C)-A\bigr),\end{align}
P\bigl(A^c\cap(B\cup C)\bigr)=P(A\cup B\cup C)-P(A).
P(X)=P(X\cap Y)+P(X\cap Y^c)
P(Y)=P(X\cap Y)+P(X^c\cap Y).
